<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Henry, Alexander. Travels in the Red River Department (Abridged), 1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0024</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">2</span>
</p>
<p><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p>July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">visit the Mississourie in order to purchase horses.  I did not approve of this Visit and endeavoured to persuade them from undertaking the Journey.  We passed a very disagreeable night<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The weath was sultry we had lightning and rain in abundance and the musquitoes were intolerable.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday 8<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">At day light mounted and proceeded &#8212; I beleive some of the Indians would have accompanied us did not the rain prevented them.  I felt happy at this as they would have been troublesome in the Journey.  Came to the white horse plains.  Here we Encamped for the night.  Our horses much fatigued from great heat and bad roads<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday 9<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Fine weather &#8212; but warm &#8212; left the river and directed our couse to the north west in order to keep clear of <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Marrais</span>, and low meadows which we supposed to be overflown<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  At Ten fell in with the great Road that leads to Lac plat and soon after overtook M<sup>r</sup> Dorion with a load of Buffaloe meat.  Directing our Course SS.W. we arrived at Portage des Prairies after a good days travelling upon a light Soil of a sandy nature which absorbed the rain as it fell.  Here I found just <span class="AddHand-author">then</span> arrived from M<sup>r</sup> Chaboillez.  The Indians of the place having been absent Since the first of June the people were in a state of Starvation<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The company have an excellent garden at this place which produces all kinds of vegetables viz. Indian Corn, Potatoes, turnips, Carrots, onions &amp;c &amp;c<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday 10<sup>th</sup> </p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Fine weather.  I found myself very unwell with a high fever but however made preparations for my journey</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">Friday</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[6]</span></p>

